commit.message:
Improve encoding detection, use MIT package (#74)

This change switches from `chardet` (an LGPL-licensed dependency) to
`charset-normalizer` -- an MIT-compatible library that should match the
license on this project & provide full `chardet` compatibility.

Other changes:

- decline to override `encoding` if it's directly specified
- properly handle file pointers: Previously, we'd only call `.close()`
  if file iteration & `chardet` detection completed without errors.

https://github.com/Ousret/charset_normalizer/blob/65b7b49655a39b91b92b9d5da57cff6032c5e5ec/charset_normalizer/models.py#L252-L256

commit.message:
Add dependency on pyramid-mako, allowing newer pyramid versions (#69)

This package currently depends on pyramid 1.4, which is very old. The reason for
this appears to be that pyramid 1.5 split mako support into a separate package.
This commit adds a dependency on pyramid-mako and increases the minimum pyramid
version to 1.5.
